div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington, Northen Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Antonio Bisegna, alias Disegnba, for Writ of Habeas Corpus, } No. 2679. Writ of Habeas Corpus.
United States of America Western District of Washington. } ss:
The President of the United States of America, to Henry M. White, United States Commissioner of Immigration, Gretting:

You are hereby commanded to ahve the body of Antonio Bisegna, by you imprisoned and detained in the King County jail, Seattle, in said County, State of Washington, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, before the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division, at the court room of the said Court, on the 20th day of Feburary, 1914, at 10 o'clock in the am. of that say, to do and recieve what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Antonio Bisegna. And have you then and there this Writ.
Witness the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the above entitled Court this 16th day of Feburary, 1914.
A
Attest my hand and seal of the said Court the day and year last above written.
div1.ab: Frank L. Crosby Clerk, By Ed M Lakin Deputy.

Return on Service of Writ.
United States of America, Western District of Washington }ss:

I hereby certify and return that I served the annexed Writ of Habeas Corpus on the therein-named Henry M. White, United States Commissioner of Immigration by handing to and leaving a true and correct copy thereof with John H. Sargent, Assistant United States Commissioner of Immigration personally at Seattle in said District on the 17th day of Febuirary A.D. 1914
Marshal's fees $2.18
By John D. Downey Deputy
In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the Matter of the Application of Antonio Bisegna F For a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington Northern Division Feb 17 1914 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk, By EML Deputy
